, who claims he was an old friend of Noreen's late husband, and Donald and Jacqueline have brought all members of the Middlesbrough Swingers Association to stay with them at the Solana. Mel lies to the Garveys that he was working in [[Morocco]], but it turns out he was in hospital in a critical condition. Whilst at the Benidorm Palace Christmas Show, the Garveys received a heartbreaking phonecall when the nurse who spoke to Mick confirmed that  Mel had died.*\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Hugh Sachs]] as Gavin Ramsbottom.<br />\n\n'''Return of''' [[Tim Healy (actor)|Tim Healy]] as Les/Lesley Conroy.<br />\n\n'''Guest starring [[Su Pollard]], [[Brian Murphy (actor)|Brian Murphy]], [[Louie Spence]], [[Asa Elliott]] and [[Roy Wood]]'''<br />\n\n'''*This storyline was written due to Geoffrey Hutchings' actual death and this episode was dedicated to him.'''\n|LineColor= 2254A4\n}}\n}}\n\n=== [[Benidorm (series 4)|Series 4]] (2011) ===\n{{Episode table\n|background = #FFE700\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref name=\"ratings\" />\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=23\n| Title=Episode 1\n| WrittenBy=[[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy=[[Sandy Johnson (director)|Sandy Johnson]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2011|2|25|df=y}}\n|Viewers=8.61{{#tag:ref|7.51 million on ITV, 709,000 on ITV HD, 390,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary= The Garveys are back in Benidorm to discover that Madge has mysteriously disappeared with her villa sold to Cilla Black and the Benidorm Palace also sold off. Meanwhile, Les/Leslie has got a new job as a barman at the Solana, much to Mateo's disapproval. Liam (Les's son) has a crush on new holidaymaker Natalie, who is accompanied by her close friend Sam. Kenneth, an employee at Troy & Gavin's salon, has joined Gavin, taking Troy's place whilst he is back in the UK tending to his critically ill long-lost fa