rm series 10.  \ud83c\udf34}}</ref> Derren Litten will make his directorial debut in the final two episodes of the series.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DerrenLitten|author=Derren Litten|number=844115883761045504|date=21 March 2017|title=Triple time. #WriterDirectorExecProducer #SheWorksHardForTheMoney}}</ref> The series began airing on 28 February 2018 on ITV at 9pm, one week after a documentary titled Benidorm: 10 Years on Holiday. This documentary show cast, past and present talking about their experience on the show and includes footage of the 10th series being filmed. This documentary aired on the 20 February 2018.\n\nAll main cast members from series nine will return, except for [[Danny Walters (actor)|Danny Walters]], [[Paul Bazely]], [[Johnny Vegas]] and [[Honor Kneafsey]]. [[Shane Richie]], who last appeared in series 8, will make his return as Sammy Valentino for four episodes. [[John Challis]] will become a series regular, after making on-off appearances for the last few series as Monty Staines. [[Tim Healy (actor)|Tim Healy]] will return full-time as transvestite Les Conroy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/shane-richie-will-return-10th-series-benidorm-455837/|title=Shane Richie will return for Benidorm series 10|date=2 March 2017|website=Whatsontv.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\nThis series will also feature an array of guest stars including children's TV comedy duo [[The Chuckle Brothers]], legendary comedian [[Bobby Ball]] and singers [[Holly Johnson]], [[Carol Decker]] and [[Tony Hadley]]. Plus another comic duo, [[Hale and Pace]] will star as undercover detectives investigating Lesley as well as actors [[Claire Sweeney]] as Maxine a snooty holiday rep and [[Nigel Havers]] returning as conman dentist Stanley. Young comedy star [[Layton Williams]] will also appear in the series in episode 9. Another notable appearance is that of [[Mark Heap]], returning as \"Malcolm\" the oddball mystery ex of Pauline and Kenneth.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-01-28/who-is-guest-starring-in-benidorm-series-10/|title=Who is guest-starring in Benidorm series 10?|website=Radiotimes.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table\n|background = #800080\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref name=\"barb.co.uk\"/>\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=66\n| Title=Episode 1\n| WrittenBy= [[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy= [[David Sant]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|2|28|df=y}}\n|Viewers= 5.77\n| ShortSummary= It's the day of Monty and Joyce's wedding, but almost from the very beginning, their happiest day seems riddled with everything going wrong in melodramatic style involving Mr Wu's banquet, Sir Henry as the very unwelcome substitute priest, seasickness and an outrageously offensive best man speech from Mateo. As the wedding is in turmoil, Kenneth steps up to the plate and risks his life to save everyone. Elsewhere, Sheron and Billy return to the Solana to enjoy their Silver Wedding anniversary, but fear that bickering Loretta and Eddie, who have for some reason also joined them for the celebrations, will not approve of Rob and his new pal Cyd when they get there. Stanley Keen returns to Blow and Go, planning to set up a dentist's practice, but has to deal with the majority shareholder, Jacqueline. Could some blindsiding ridiculously white teeth persuade the widowed swinger? Plus, acting managaress Sam is roped into Dodgy Dave's  rigged raffle scam that doesn't go according to plan at all because of Dave's many crimson coloured children!\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby, [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby, [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy, [[Josh Bolt]] as Rob Dawson and [[Nathan Bryon]] as Joey Ellis.\t\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Tony Hadley]], [[Nigel Havers]], [[Michael Fenton Stevens]], Paul Chan, [[Michael Starke (actor)|Michael Starke]], [[Stuart Milligan]] and Flash Harry'''\n\n'''Dedicated to''' [[Bobby Knutt]]\n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=67\n| Title=Episode 2\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|3|7|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.89\n| ShortSummary= With Eddie and Loretta awaiting their grandson's arrival, Sheron and Billy learn the terrifying truth when Rob and Cyd finally check in to the Solana. The wedding party are also back at the Solana, but Kenneth is noticeably absent from the crowd having become lost at sea. But there is happy endings all round when Kenneth emerges from the waves with a thrilling tale to tell. However, what will he think of Stanley and all his dental instruments of torture in Blow & Go? Elsewhere, dim-witted regular Joey checks in, but instead of going with Tiger, he has come with his new Irish friend Callum.\n\n'''First appearance of''' Laila Zaidi as Cyd and Julian Moore-Cook as Callum.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby, [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby and [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Nigel Havers]]'''\n\n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=68\n| Title=Episode 3\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|3|14|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.15\n| ShortSummary= Monty has been appointed as the hotel's entertainments manager by Joyce and throws himself into work by planning a 'magical' evening that the guests won't forget any time soon, but for the right reasons? Meanwhile, it is looking like a day of romance for Kenneth and Callum, while the Dawson family hold their suspicions over Cyd. Also, Liam is back at the Solana and reunites with his most loved ones.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby and [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[The Chuckle Brothers]], David O\u2019Reilly, Gina Fillingham and Antonio de la Cruz'''\n| Line