\n| EpisodeNumber=71\n| Title=Episode 6\n| WrittenBy= Mark Brotherhood\n| DirectedBy= Duncan Foster\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|4|11|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.70\n| ShortSummary= Noreen senses that her more glamorous identical twin Doreen is about, while Sammy is still giddy from his comeback performance and decides to make his Neptune\u2019s debut, but there is a twist coming as his shockingly strange past catches up with him, involving a ventriloquist's dummy and an obsessive fan. Elsewhere, Rob races against time to get his beautiful Cyd back from her father, prompted by Mateo\u2019s terrible wisdom - however, Billy and Eddie can't help but get involved, because of a suggestion Eddie makes regarding ''[[Breaking Bad]]''.\n\n'''Note:''' This episode features the debut of Doreen, played by [[Elsie Kelly]] who also plays Noreen in the series. Because there is one actress portraying two characters, Jane Hollington has joined the cast as a double for Noreen and Doreen.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Tim Healy (actor)|Tim Healy]] as Les/Lesley Conroy.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Josh Bolt]] as Rob Dawson and Laila Zaidi as Cyd.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Shane Richie]], [[Hale and Pace]], [[Gary Oliver (actor)|Gary Oliver]], [[Graeme Hawley]], John-Paul Jones and Daniel Garcia''' \n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=72\n| Title=Episode 7\n| WrittenBy= Mark Brotherhood\n| DirectedBy= Duncan Foster\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|4|18|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.36\n| ShortSummary= After Sammy performs some disastrous acts in Neptune\u2019s, a furious Joyce wants him out. What will she think when Monty gives Sammy a contract? Meanwhile, Doreen decides to send Pauline\u2019s novel off to the publishers and Dennis and Nigel find themselves growing reluctant to arresting Lesley. With Rob and Cyd off in Paris, Billy and Sheron relive their youth together and Mateo may be facing an unwelcome trip. Elsewhere, Doreen introduces Noreen and Pauline to her boyfriend - who is revealed to be Malcolm, who has a very sinister plan in store.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby, [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby and [[Tim Healy (actor)|Tim Healy]] as Les/Lesley Conroy.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Mark Heap]], [[Shane Richie]], [[Hale and Pace]], Danny Tetley and Rochelle Hamilton'''\n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=73\n| Title=Episode 8\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= Derren Litten\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|4|25|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.14\n| ShortSummary= Monty is in need of a new job after being sacked by Joyce, and has to decide whether to swallow his pride and go to Sir Henry, or see if Mr Wu has a fitting position for him. Meanwhile, Loretta and Eddie make secret plans for an anniversary party for Billy and Sheron back in the UK, but it looks as if the couple are making plans of their own. Elsewhere, things are not going well for Kenneth as he wakes up in Blow & Go after a big night out, only to realise that the builders have inadvertently bricked him in.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Michael Fenton Stevens]], Paul Chan, John-Paul Jones and [[Philip Pope]]''' \n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=74\n| Title=Episode 9\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= Derren Litten\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|5|2|df=y}}\n|Viewers= 4.13\n| ShortSummary= A strike in the airport by the baggage handlers causes panic at the Solana, and the Dawsons rush to catch their flight with Billy and Sheron's anniversary plans now in jeopardy as they may not make it back to the UK to celebrate. Meanwhile, Kenneth is on the warpath with Temple-Savage after his accidental imprisonment the previous day, and Joyce worries about the rumours that Crystal Hennessy-Vass may be letting the Solana go. Elsewhere, Sam's old flame Angelo is in town, devastating Joey, and misunderstandings are finally resolved between Monty and Joyce.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Jake Canuso]] as Mateo Castellanos, [[Janine Duvitski]] as Jacqueline Stewart, [[Tony Maudsley]] as Kenneth Du Beke, [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy, [[Shelley Longworth]] as Sam Wood, [[Sherrie Hewson]] as Joyce Temple-Savage, [[John Challis]] as Monty Staines, [[Julie Graham]] as Sheron Dawson, [[Steve Edge]] as Billy Dawson, [[Bobby Knutt]] as Eddie Dawson, [[Nathan Bryon]] as Joey Ellis, [[Kate Fitzgerald]] as Loretta Chase and Julian Moore-Cook as Callum.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Bobby Ball]], [[Michael Fenton Stevens]], [[James Lance]], [[Derren Litten]], [[Claire Sweeney]], [[Layton Williams]], John-Paul Jones, Ashley Rebanks and [[Holly Johnson]]''' \n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n}}\n\n== Ratings ==\n{{Television ratings graph\n| title     = Benidorm\n| country   = UK\n| color1    = #000000\n| color2    = #744626\n| color3    = #B11518\n| color4    = #FFE700\n| color5    = #BB76FF\n| color6    = #94E77F\n| color7    = #F46D29\n| color8    = #F378A9\n| color9    = #21476C\n| color10  = #800080\n| bar_width = 9\n| average   = y\n| x_intervals = 5\n| y_intervals = 2\n|-\n<!-- S01E01 -->| 5.86\n<!-- S01E02 -->| 4.86\n<!-- S01E03 -->| 3.88\n<!-- S01E04 -->| 4.02\n<!-- S01E05 -->| 3.85\n<!-- S01E06 -->| 4.13\n<!-- S01_AV -->| 4.43\n|-\n<!-- S02E01 -->| 7.14\n<!-- S02E02 -->| 6.05\n<!-- S02E03 -->| 5.59\n<!-- S02E04 -->| 6.29\n<!-- S02E05 -->| 5.70\n<!-- S02E06 -->| 5.21\n<!-- S02E07 -->| 5.57\n<!-- S02E08 -->| 6.32\n<!-- S02_AV -->| 5.98\n|-\n<!-- S03E01 -->| 6.50\n<!-- S03E02 -->| 6.17\n<!-- S03E03 -->| 6.38\n<!-- S03E04 -->| 6.68\n<!-- S03E05 -->| 6.61\n<!-- S03E06 -->| 6.80\n<!-- S03_AV -->| 6.52\n|-\n<!-- S04E01 -->| 8.61\n<!-- S04E02 -->| 8.11\n<!-- S04E03 -->| 7.43\n<!-- S04E04 -->| 7.41\n<!-- S04E05 -->| 7.24\n<!-- S04E06 -->| 7.82\n<!-- S04_AV -->| 7.77\n|-\n<!-- S05E01 -->| 7.72\n<!-- S05E02 -->| 7.42\n<!-- S05E03 -->| 7.56\n<!-- S05E04 -->| 7.06\n<!-- S05E05 -->| 6.41\n<!-- S05E06 -->| 6.90\n<!-- S05E07 -->| 6.37\n<!-- S05_AV -->| 7.06\n|-\n<!-- S06E01 -->| 7.95\n<!-- S06E02 -->| 6.9