y}}\n|Viewers=4.86\n| ShortSummary=The Garvey family is calming down after discovering Chantelle's secret pregnancy. However, Madge is quick to stir up trouble. Meanwhile, Martin tries to cheer Kate up with a trip into Benidorm, with disastrous results when they encounter the legendary \"[[Sticky Vicky]]\", and Geoff is attempting to break a world record for holding his breath underwater.\n| LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=3\n| Title=Busy Boy\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Kevin Allen\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|15|df=y}}\n|Viewers=3.88\n| ShortSummary=Kelly, who works at The Solana, has just got engaged to womanising barman Mateo, leaving Donald and Jacqueline worried. But Mateo seems more interested in Kate, and the unlikely pair soon end up having a passionate encounter. But will Martin discover his wife's betrayal? Meanwhile, Chantelle's pregnancy ends up pushing her and Janice closer together, whilst Geoff and Noreen do a duet at the karaoke.\n\n'''Guest starring [[Niky Wardley]] and Paul Smith'''\n| LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode List\n| EpisodeNumber=4\n| Title=A Civilised Couple\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Kevin Allen\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|2|22|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.02\n| ShortSummary=Madge is tricked into believing that Donald and Jacqueline are a sociable couple. They mistake Madge for a swinger, and things get out of hand. Meanwhile, Martin is upbeat now that his mart\u00eda simple Suffolk seems to be back on track. But Kate feels guilty after her encounter with Mateo. Elsewhere, Janice becomes jealous of Suzie, a geordie girl who seems to have hit it off with Mick, whilst Mateo seduces another holidaymaker - Troy.\n\n'''Guest starring Paul Smith'''\n| LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=5\n| Title=The Return Of The Oracle\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Kevin Allen\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|3|1|df=y}}\n|Viewers=3.85\n| ShortSummary=It's quiz night at The Solana, and the ''Oracle'' (Geoff) believes that this is his big moment. However, Geoff was so angry when he didn't win, he revealed shocking secrets that could tear lives apart. Meanwhile, Donald tries to save Gavin and Troy's relationship after Troy's shocking betrayal with Mateo, whilst Kate confides in Madge about the problems in her marriage.\n\n'''Guest starring Paul Smith'''\n| LineColor=000000\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=6\n| Title=The Beach\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Kevin Allen\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2007|3|8|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.13\n| ShortSummary=After the Garveys win their \u20ac100 prize from last night's quiz, they decide to go to the beach - though Madge has invited Donald and Jacqueline, much to the disapproval of miserly Mick. Later back at the Solana, Kate is scarred for life after picking up faeces in the swimming pool. Meanwhile, a con artist tries her luck with the holidaymakers - and the Garveys find themselves in trouble , when Mick's past comes back to haunt him.\n\n'''Guest starring [[Ella Kenion]] and Paul Smith'''\n| LineColor=000000\n}}\n}}\n\n=== Series 2 (2008) ===\n{{Episode table\n|background = #744626\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref name=\"ratings\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-30?|date=|accessdate=|publisher=[[BARB]]|title=Weekly Viewing Summary (see relevant week)}}</ref>\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=7\n| Title=In The Deep End\n| WrittenBy=[[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy=[[Sandy Johnson (director)|Sandy Johnson]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2008|3|28|df=y}}\n|Viewers=7.14\n| ShortSummary=The Garveys and the rest of the holidaymakers return for another week in Benidorm - even with a few new members of the family. These include Madge's new boyfriend Mel (whom she has only known for a few weeks), plus Chantelle's baby son Coolio. Martin and Kate escape the horrors of their last holiday by staying in Altea, but a problem with the room leads to Kate facing her worst nightmare. Later, a diving competition between Mel and Geoff turns into a tragic life-threatening incident.\n\n'''First appearance of''' [[Geoffrey Hutchings]] as Mel.\n| LineColor= 744626\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=8\n| Title=The Babysitters\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2008|4|4|df=y}}\n|Viewers=6.05\n| ShortSummary=Chantelle asks Martin and Kate to babysit Coolio for the night, which ends in him liking Martin. Mel's recovery from the diving accident might not have helped his singing voice when his karaoke at Neptune's goes sour. After the singing, Mel proposes to Madge - and tries to do it romantically, but fails due to his bad back.\n| LineColor= 744626\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=9\n| Title=The Arm-Wrestling Competition\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2008|4|11|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.59\n| ShortSummary=Madge and Janice's mother-and-daughter relationship turns sour, when she tries to persuade Madge not to marry Mel. Meanwhile, Geoff and his mum Noreen organise their own arm-wrestling competition, with Mick being beaten by Jacqueline due to her \"strong wrists\".\n| LineColor= 744626\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=10\n| Title=The Bullfight\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2008|4|18|df=y}}\n|Viewers=6.29\n| ShortSummary=The holidaymakers are up for a coach trip to see a free bullfight, but Madge has terrible diarrhoea - making them late by stopping all the time. Just as the holidaymakers thought things couldn't possibly get any worse, Janey tries to flog \u20ac200 electric juicers. Unfortunately, she had to sell at least one juicer or the holidaymakers were not allowed to watch the fight. To stop the fuss, Mel agrees to buy one - then realises it was \u20ac200. Just after the holidaymakers were allowed to see the bullfight, it doesn't go as planned - it turns out the bull was replaced by a dog with fake horns. During the bullfight, the electric juicer that Mel purchased had blown up. To everyone's shock, Kate announces he is dead - until he wakes up, scaring everybody. Meanwhile at the Solana, Geoff and Chantelle decided not to see the bullfight, and instead have a few burgers on the poolside with each other and baby Coolio.\n| LineColor= 744626\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=11\n| Title=The Mother Of The Ex\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2008|4|25|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.70\n| ShortSummary=Ex-hotel worker Kelly is back, this time with her cockney mother, Sylvia. As Sylvia's mobility scooter stops working, Mel offers to fix it, but Michael and Chantelle think he is kissing her. Madge then finds out about the incident, not knowing it was a misunderstanding - and begins a poolside showdown with her.\n\n'''Guest starring [[Niky Wardley]] and [[Wendy Richard]]'''\n| LineColor= 744626\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=12\n| Title=Second Thoughts\n| WrittenBy=Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy=Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2008|5|2|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.21\n| ShortSummary=\nIn their last effort, Mick and Janice both try to persuade Madge not to get married. Meanwhile, Mick has upset Janice, by forgetting it's their 10th wedding anniversary. Janice tries her best to give him hints, but he is still not aware of the occasion. That morning, Janice goes to a local bar for a drink with Madge, and finds out the owner, Jack, has a crush on her. As Janice forgot her money, Jack told Janice she could pay him with a kiss. As her mother leaves, she secretly snogs Jack - but she soon found out that was a mistake, as he quickly became obsessed with her. Later that night in Neptune's, Janice cries and opens up to Mick, finally revealing 