sdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> All main characters from series 6 returned except for [[Kenny Ireland]], [[Hannah Waddingham]] and [[Bel Powley]]. Filming for the seventh series began on 24 March 2014.<ref name=\"twitter1\"/> [[Kenny Ireland]], who played Donald, wasn't in this series. His character was written out because the actor had developed cancer. He died in July of the same year and the final episode was dedicated to him. All ratings do not include HD as it isn't available for all the episodes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-28587475|title=Actor Kenny Ireland dies aged 68|date=31 July 2014|accessdate=2 October 2018|website=Bbc.co.uk}}</ref> It was also confirmed that the Garveys will leave during series seven.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DerrenLitten|author=Derren Litten|number=447011525145133056|date=21 March 2014|title=Yes, it's true, The Garveys will be leaving during series VII. But as we all know, in Benidorm, it's always adios and never goodbye.}}</ref>\nThe seven-part seventh series began on [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]] on 2 January 2015 at 9pm and finished on 13 February 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.comedy.co.uk/guide/tv/benidorm/episodes/7/1/|title=Benidorm Series 7, Episode 1 - British Comedy Guide|first=British Comedy|last=Guide|website=British Comedy Guide|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n{{Episode table\n|background = #F46D29\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref>Based on 28 day data from BARB</ref>\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=43\n| Title=Episode 1 \n| WrittenBy= [[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy= [[David Sant]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|1|2|df=y}}\n|Viewers=7.27{{#tag:ref|5.72 million on ITV, 1.04 million on ITV HD, 510,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary=The Solana staff are angry, as everyone has been given a pay cut. Tiger Dyke is angry too - his cards and cash have been stolen, so he's relying on his Dad. The Garveys are worried Madge is being stalked, while Jacqueline is holidaying without Donald: they've arranged a wife swap to mark their wedding anniversary - so she arrives with [[Welsh people|Welshman]] Glynn.\n\n'''First appearance of''' [[Alan David (actor)|Alan David]] as Glynn Flint and [[Charlotte Eaton (actress)|Charlotte Eaton]] as Terri Dawson.<br />\n\n'''Guest starring [[Leslie Jordan]]'''\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=44\n| Title=Episode 2 \n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|1|9|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.41{{#tag:ref|4.84 million on ITV, 574,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary=  The Garveys meet a guy called Buck A. Roo who reveals that Madge is about to inherit millions from the Collins family, making Joyce become suspicious, she orders Lesley to investigate, this evidence changes Madges mind making her want to leave, the Garveys then leave for Las Vegas. Meanwhile, Kenneth takes advantage of a psychic customer; Psychic Sue, and holds a s\u00e9ance to contact his mum - but the message he receives appears to be for Madge, from an old Benidorm friend Melvin Churchill Harvey.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Charlotte Eaton (actress)|Charlotte Eaton]] as Terri Dawson.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Steve Pemberton]] as Mick Garvey, [[Siobhan Finneran]] as Janice Garvey and [[Oliver Stokes]] as Michael Garvey <br />\n\n'''Guest starring [[Amanda Barrie]] and [[Leslie Jordan]]'''\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=45\n| Title=Episode 3\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|1|16|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.45{{#tag:ref|4.76 million on ITV, 687,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary=Joyce becomes suspicious when Blow and Go appears extremely busy, and how young its customers are looking - even an unusually fresh-faced Mateo. Joyce confronts Kenneth, who is forced to offer her free botox sessions to avoid his secret being reported to head office. Still annoyed at his dad, Tiger hides the news that Auntie Terri is on her way to the Solana resort.\n\n'''Return of''' [[Johnny Vegas]] as Geoff Maltby and [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby.\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=46\n| Title=Episode 4\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|1|23|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.47{{#tag:ref|4.70 million on ITV, 767,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary= Liam receives a surprise visit from his mum - Les's ex Gloria. The Oracle is hoping to impress the other guests and staff by walking barefoot across hot coals, and catches Terri's eye in the process.\n\n'''Guest starring [[Denise Black]] and Paul Chan'''\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=47\n| Title=Episode 5\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= [[Sandy Johnson (director)|Sandy Johnson]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|1|30|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.40{{#tag:ref|4.80 million on ITV, 602,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary=Inspired by a pep-talk from Crystal, Kenneth and Liam launch a Blow and Go makeover competition. Crystal Hennessy-Vass announces that the staff budget is being cut by half - and Joyce is being replaced by Janey, her predecessor. As Geoff's Romanian fiancee Ionela arrives in Benidorm, Noreen discovers that Geoff has told her he is a successful businessman.\n\n'''Return of''' [[Crissy Rock]] as Janey York.\n\n'''Guest starring  [[Alice Barlow]], [[Joan Collins]] and Milanka Brooks'''\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=48\n| Title=Episode 6\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|2|6|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.79{{#tag:ref|4.10 million on ITV, 689,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary=Jason is back but what is his connection to Janey York? Clive gets swindled out of 5,000 euros by dodgy estate agents Monty and Melanie. The Oracle and Noreen are stuck in a lift, discovering all sorts about each other.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Crissy Rock]] as Janey York.\n\n'''Guest starring [[Philip Olivier]], [[Alice Barlow]], [[Nadia Sawalha]], [[John Challis]] and Milanka Brooks'''\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=49\n| Title=Episode 7\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= Sandy Johnson\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|2|13|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.40{{#tag:ref|4.72 million on ITV, 681,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary= Mateo reveals his home life is a disaster, his mother-in-law Dolores is threatening to kill him, so Lesley urges the barman to move out and start a new life. Clive, Tiger and Terri come up with a plan to retrieve Clive's 5,000 euros from dodgy property developer Monty - while Glynn's wife, Rhiannon, arrives at the Solana resort; but there's no sign of Donald.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Johnny Vegas]] as Geoff Maltby and [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby.<br />\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy, [[Perry Benson]] as Clive Dyke, [[Charlotte Eaton (actress)|Charlotte Eaton]] as Terri Dawson and [[Alan David (actor)|Alan David]] as Glynn Flint.<br />\n\n'''Guest starring [[Alice Barlow]], [[Nadia Sawalha]], [[John Challis]], [[Amanda Barrie]] and [[Ruth Madoc]]'''\n\n'''Dedicated to''' [[Kenny Ireland]]\n| LineColor=F46D29\n}}\n}}\n\n=== Series 8 (2016) ===\nA 7-episode eighth series was ordered on 6 February 2015. All episodes were written by [[Derren Litten]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a626961/benidorm-commissioned-for-eighth-series-by-itv.html|title=Benidorm commissioned for eighth series|date=6 February 2015|website=Digitalspy.co.uk|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref> On 26 March 2015 it was announced that Series 8 will introduce a new family, the Dawsons. [[Julie Graham]], [[Steve Edge]], [[Bobby Knutt]], [[Josh Bolt]] and [[Honor Kneafsey]] had been cast as Sheron Dawson, Billy Dawson, Eddie Dawson, Rob Dawson and Jodie Dawson, respectively. Series 8 also introduced Jessica Ellerby and [[Nathan Bryon]] as Amber Platt and Joey Ellis. Filming began on 23 March 2015 and ended on 25 June 2015. It began airing on 11 January 2016 and finished on 22 February 2016.<ref name=\"Series 8 Air Dates\">{{cite web|url=http://www.comedy.co.uk/guide/tv/benidorm/episodes/8/|title=Benidorm Series 8 episode guide - British Comedy Guide|first=British Comedy|last=Guide|website=British Comedy Guide|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n{{Episode table\n|background = #F378A9\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref name=\"barb.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.barb.co.uk/whats-new/weekly-top-30?|title=Weekly top 30 programmes - BARB|website=Barb.co.uk|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=50\n| Title=Episode 1\n| WrittenBy= [[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy= [[Robin Shepperd]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|1|11|df=y}}\n|Viewers=6.82{{#tag:ref|4.91 million on ITV, 1.30 million on ITV HD, 613,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}}<ref name=\"28 day data\">28 day data</ref>\n| ShortSummary= The Dawsons check-in at the Solana, Billy is worried about telling wife Sheron that his father Eddie is moving in with them when they get home. Joyce is desperate for more staff and must choose between unqualified, but outrageously flirtatious Marcus and efficient Amber. Meanwhile, Jacqueline, Kenneth and Troy scatter Donald's ashes from the cross, and Tiger arrives with new friend Joey.\n\n'''First appearance of''' [[Julie Graham]] as Sheron Dawson, [[Steve Edge]] as Billy Dawson, [[Bobby Knutt]] as Eddie Dawson, [[Josh Bolt]] as Rob Dawson, [[Honor Kneafsey]] as Jodie Dawson, Jessica Ellerby as Amber Platt and [[Nathan Bryon]] as Joey Ellis.<br />\n\n'''Return of''' [[Paul Bazely]] as Troy Ramsbottom.<br />\n\n'''Absent:'''