es an intervention to help Pauline who's fallen off the wagon. Billy and Sheron leave Eddie in charge of the kids for the day and Joyce Temple Savage has got an admirer.\n\n'''Guest starring [[John Challis]]'''\n| LineColor=F378A9\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=54\n| Title=Episode 5\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten & Gaby Hull\n| DirectedBy= [[David Sant]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|2|8|df=y}}\n|Viewers=6.09{{#tag:ref|4.43 million on ITV, 1.15 million on ITV HD, 513,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}}<ref name=\"28 day data\"/>\n| ShortSummary=Tiger and Joey take on a mountain challenge with little provisions - will they make it back in one piece? Romance is in the air at the Solana but Mateo could be in trouble when a violent stranger starts making enquiries about him at the hotel.\n\n'''Guest starring Milanka Brooks & [[Angus Deayton]]'''\n| LineColor=F378A9\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=55\n| Title=Episode 6\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten & Gaby Hull\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|2|15|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.84{{#tag:ref|4.32 million on ITV, 521,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}}<ref name=\"28 day data\"/> \n| ShortSummary=Benidorm is gearing up for the fancy dress British Fiesta. The boys' ingenious costumes get them in trouble with the law and Les misses Liam. Mateo scares the punters in his clown costume and Troy is harassed by an unwanted and unstable admirer...\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Johnny Vegas]] as Geoff Maltby, [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby and [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby.\n\n'''Guest starring [[Frances Barber]]'''\n| LineColor=F378A9\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=56\n| Title=Episode 7\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2016|2|22|df=y}}\n|Viewers=4.68{{#tag:ref|4.22 million on ITV, 463,000 on ITV +1|group=nb}} \n| ShortSummary=The Pride of Benidorm Awards are at the Solana and sleazy comp\u00e8re, Sammy Valentino, is causing trouble. Jodi's acting career gets a boost and Blow & Go are awaiting a mystery new stylist. Crystal brings the house down with a special performance.\n\n'''Return of''' [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Johnny Vegas]] as Geoff Maltby, [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby and [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' Jessica Ellerby as Amber Platt.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Shane Richie]], [[Joan Collins]], [[Michael Fenton Stevens]], [[John Challis]] and [[Kevin Bishop]]''' \n| LineColor=F378A9\n}}\n}}\n\n===Series 9 (2017)===\nThe show was renewed for a ninth series on 22 February 2016 and filming took place between 14 March 2016 and 14 July 2016. Series 9 premiered on 1 March 2017 and ended on 3 May 2017. It consists of nine episodes, an increase on the previous series. All main cast members from series 8 returned, except from Jessica Ellerby. [[Shelley Longworth]] makes her return as Sam Wood, after her last appearance in series 5. [[Adam Gillen]] returns as a regular, following Liam's return in the series 8 finale. [[Tim Healy (actor)|Tim Healy]] was hospitalised during filming, with Les/Lesley only appearing in the first four episodes.\n\n{{Episode table\n|background = #21476C\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref name=\"barb.co.uk\"/>\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=57\n| Title=Episode 1\n| WrittenBy= [[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy= [[Robin Shepperd]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2017|3|1|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.79\n| ShortSummary= The Dawsons' holiday starts with a bang when Eddie has an accident and Sheron's fashion taste is put into question. An old inheritance puts a smile Kenneth's face. Meanwhile, Tiger and Joey are in a party mood as Sam, the new holiday rep and former guest at the Solana, takes them under her wing.\n\n'''First appearance of''' [[Kate Fitzgerald]] as Loretta Chase.<br />\n\n'''Absent:''' [