hortSummary= First screened in 2007 in a 30-minute format, the show has grown to be hugely popular with ITV viewers and has been BAFTA nominated and won numerous TV awards over the years including two National TV Awards.\n \nThe show\u2019s creator and writer Derren Litten will guide viewers around Benidorm to reveal all about how the show was created whilst visiting the show\u2019s many real life locations.  Cast (past and present) will talk about their roles on the show alongside show bloopers and exclusive behind the scenes footage of the upcoming 10th series being filmed.\n \nAll the Garvey family return for the one off special \u2013 Steve Pemberton, Siobhan Finneran, Sheila Reid, Ollie Stokes and Hannah Hobley talk about their time on the show.\n\n|LineColor= #006600\n}}\n}}\n\n===Series 10 (2018)===\nA tenth series has also been commissioned. Filming began on 13 March 2017 and ended on 12 July 2017. The first episode was directed by [[David Sant]].<ref>{{cite tweet|user=BenidormTVshow|author=Benidorm|number=841252431841370113|date=13 March 2017|title=And we're off! Day 1 of shooting #Benidorm series 10.  \ud83c\udf34}}</ref> Derren Litten will make his directorial debut in the final two episodes of the series.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=DerrenLitten|author=Derren Litten|number=844115883761045504|date=21 March 2017|title=Triple time. #WriterDirectorExecProducer #SheWorksHardForTheMoney}}</ref> The series began airing on 28 February 2018 on ITV at 9pm, one week after a documentary titled Benidorm: 10 Years on Holiday. This documentary show cast, past and present talking about their experience on the show and includes footage of the 10th series being filmed. This documentary aired on the 20 February 2018.\n\nAll main cast members from series nine will return, except for [[Danny Walters (actor)|Danny Walters]], [[Paul Bazely]], [[Johnny Vegas]] and [[Honor Kneafsey]]. [[Shane Richie]], who last appeared in series 8, will make his return as Sammy Valentino for four episodes. [[John Challis]] will become a series regular, after making on-off appearances for the last few series as Monty Staines. [[Tim Healy (actor)|Tim Healy]] will return full-time as transvestite Les Conroy.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.whatsontv.co.uk/news/shane-richie-will-return-10th-series-benidorm-455837/|title=Shane Richie will return for Benidorm series 10|date=2 March 2017|website=Whatsontv.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\nThis series will also feature an array of guest stars including children's TV comedy duo [[The Chuckle Brothers]], legendary comedian [[Bobby Ball]] and singers [[Holly Johnson]], [[Carol Decker]] and [[Tony Hadley]]. Plus another comic duo, [[Hale and Pace]] will star as undercover detectives investigating Lesley as well as actors [[Claire Sweeney]] as Maxine a snooty holiday rep and [[Nigel Havers]] returning as conman dentist Stanley. Young comedy star [[Layton Williams]] will also appear in the series in episode 9. Another notable appearance is that of [[Mark Heap]], returning as \"Malcolm\" the oddball mystery ex of Pauline and Kenneth.\n<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/tv/2018-01-28/who-is-guest-starring-in-benidorm-series-10/|title=Who is guest-starring in Benidorm series 10?|website=Radiotimes.com|accessdate=2 October 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Episode table\n|background = #800080\n|overall    = \n|title      = \n|director   = \n|writer     = \n|airdate    = \n|viewers    = \n|country    = UK\n|forceoverall = y\n|titleT     = Episode\n|viewersR   = <ref name=\"barb.co.uk\"/>\n|episodes   = \n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=66\n| Title=Episode 1\n| WrittenBy= [[Derren Litten]]\n| DirectedBy= [[David Sant]]\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|2|28|df=y}}\n|Viewers= 5.77\n| ShortSummary= It's the day of Monty and Joyce's wedding, but almost from the very beginning, their happiest day seems riddled with everything going wrong in melodramatic style involving Mr Wu's banquet, Sir Henry as the very unwelcome substitute 