 with his new Irish friend Callum.\n\n'''First appearance of''' Laila Zaidi as Cyd and Julian Moore-Cook as Callum.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby, [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby and [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Nigel Havers]]'''\n\n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=68\n| Title=Episode 3\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|3|14|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.15\n| ShortSummary= Monty has been appointed as the hotel's entertainments manager by Joyce and throws himself into work by planning a 'magical' evening that the guests won't forget any time soon, but for the right reasons? Meanwhile, it is looking like a day of romance for Kenneth and Callum, while the Dawson family hold their suspicions over Cyd. Also, Liam is back at the Solana and reunites with his most loved ones.\n\n'''Absent:''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby and [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[The Chuckle Brothers]], David O\u2019Reilly, Gina Fillingham and Antonio de la Cruz'''\n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=69\n| Title=Episode 4\n| WrittenBy= Mark Brotherhood\n| DirectedBy= David Sant\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|3|21|df=y}}\n|Viewers=5.60\n| ShortSummary= When things go very downhill for Monty as he faces the furious wrath of Joyce and his job is put on the line, there is a glimmer of hope. Could the surprise return of entertainer Sammy Valentino be the key to getting Monty's job back? Meanwhile, Jacqueline's newest business venture certainly fails to impress Liam and Kenneth and there are two very suspicious men sneaking around the Solana. Elsewhere, Eddie adds to the Dawson's family troubles and Callum is seeking a professional. \n\n'''Absent:''' [[Elsie Kelly]] as Noreen Maltby and [[Selina Griffiths]] as Pauline Maltby. \n\n'''Guest Starring [[Hale and Pace]], [[Shane Richie]], [[Carol Decker]], Barry Green, Alex 