their own. Elsewhere, things are not going well for Kenneth as he wakes up in Blow & Go after a big night out, only to realise that the builders have inadvertently bricked him in.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Michael Fenton Stevens]], Paul Chan, John-Paul Jones and [[Philip Pope]]''' \n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber=74\n| Title=Episode 9\n| WrittenBy= Derren Litten\n| DirectedBy= Derren Litten\n| OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2018|5|2|df=y}}\n|Viewers= 4.13\n| ShortSummary= A strike in the airport by the baggage handlers causes panic at the Solana, and the Dawsons rush to catch their flight with Billy and Sheron's anniversary plans now in jeopardy as they may not make it back to the UK to celebrate. Meanwhile, Kenneth is on the warpath with Temple-Savage after his accidental imprisonment the previous day, and Joyce worries about the rumours that Crystal Hennessy-Vass may be letting the Solana go. Elsewhere, Sam's old flame Angelo is in town, devastating Joey, and misunderstandings are finally resolved between Monty and Joyce.\n\n'''Last appearance of''' [[Jake Canuso]] as Mateo Castellanos, [[Janine Duvitski]] as Jacqueline Stewart, [[Tony Maudsley]] as Kenneth Du Beke, [[Adam Gillen]] as Liam Conroy, [[Shelley Longworth]] as Sam Wood, [[Sherrie Hewson]] as Joyce Temple-Savage, [[John Challis]] as Monty Staines, [[Julie Graham]] as Sheron Dawson, [[Steve Edge]] as Billy Dawson, [[Bobby Knutt]] as Eddie Dawson, [[Nathan Bryon]] as Joey Ellis, [[Kate Fitzgerald]] as Loretta Chase and Julian Moore-Cook as Callum.\n\n'''Guest Starring [[Bobby Ball]], [[Michael Fenton Stevens]], [[James Lance]], [[Derren Litten]], [[Claire Sweeney]], [[Layton Williams]], John-Paul Jones, Ashley Rebanks and [[Holly Johnson]]''' \n| LineColor=#800080\n}}\n}}\n\n== Ratings ==\n{{Television ratings graph\n| title     = Benidorm\n| country   = UK\n| color1    = #000000\n| color2    = #744626\n| color3    = #B11518\n| color4    = #FFE700\n| color5    = #BB76FF\n| color6    =