erican films]]\n[[Category:American romantic comedy films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Richard Thorpe]]\n[[Category:American black-and-white films]]\n[[Category:Chesterfield Pictures films]]\n[[Category:Films made before the MPAA Production Code]]\n\n{{1930s-romantic-comedy-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1932 film by Richard Thorpe}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name =  Slightly Married\n| image =\n| image_size =\n| caption =\n| director = [[Richard Thorpe]]\n| producer = [[George R. Batcheller]]\n| writer =  [[Mary McCarthy (screenwriter)|Mary McCarthy]]\n| narrator =\n| starring = [[Evalyn Knapp]]<br>[[Walter Byron (actor)|Walter Byron]]<br>[[Marie Prevost]]\n| music = [[Lee Zahler]]\n| cinematography = [[M.A. Anderson]]\n| editing = [[Roland D. Reed]]\n| studio = Invincible Pictures \n| distributor = [[Chesterfield Motion Pictures Corporation]]\n| released = October 15, 1932\n| runtime = 65 minutes\n| country = United States\n| language = English}}\n\n'''''Slightly Married''''' is a 1932 American [[Pre-Code Hollywood|pre-Code]] [[romantic comedy]] film directed by [[Richard Thorpe]] and starring [[Evalyn Knapp]], [[Walter Byron (actor)|Walter Byron]] and [[Marie Prevost]].<ref>Pitts, p. 91</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Evalyn Knapp]] as Mary Smith  \n* [[Walter Byron (actor)|Walter Byron]] as Jimmie Martin  \n* [[Marie Prevost]] as Nellie Gordon  \n* [[Jason Robards Sr.]] as Jack Haines  \n* [[Robert Ellis (actor, born 1892)|Robert Ellis]] as Brandon  \n* [[Dorothy Christy]] as Marjorie  \n* [[Clarissa Selwynne]] as Mrs. Martin \n* [[Phillips Smalley]] as Mr. Martin  \n* [[Herbert Evans (actor)|Herbert Evans]] as Hodges \n* [[Lloyd Ingraham]] as Judge  \n* [[Mary Foy (actress)|Mary Foy]] as Landlady\n* [[Al Bridge]] as Tenant  \n* [[Bobby Burns]] as Minister  \n* [[Allan Cavan]] as Banker  \n* [[Jack Pennick]] as Sailor\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* Pitts, Michael R. ''Poverty Row Studios, 1929-1940''. McFarland & Company, 2005.<!-- IS